{"parse":{"title":"International Gender Champions","pageid":57547002,"revid":853691586,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:IGC-UN-Women_publication_Launch_(International_Gender_Champions).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d0/IGC-UN-Women_publication_Launch_%28International_Gender_Champions%29.jpg/220px-IGC-UN-Women_publication_Launch_%28International_Gender_Champions%29.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"147\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d0/IGC-UN-Women_publication_Launch_%28International_Gender_Champions%29.jpg/330px-IGC-UN-Women_publication_Launch_%28International_Gender_Champions%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d0/IGC-UN-Women_publication_Launch_%28International_Gender_Champions%29.jpg/440px-IGC-UN-Women_publication_Launch_%28International_Gender_Champions%29.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"5472\" data-file-height=\"3648\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:IGC-UN-Women_publication_Launch_(International_Gender_Champions).jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Sign showing ICG logo in a library setting</div></div></div>\n<p><b>International Gender Champions</b> (<b>IGC</b>) is a network of female and male leaders of member states, international organizations, and civil society working for gender equality. It is an initiative of Women@TheTable, and was founded in 2015 by Caitlin Kraft-Buchman of Women@TheTable, Ambassador <a href=\"/wiki/Pamela_Hamamoto\" title=\"Pamela Hamamoto\">Pam Hamamoto</a>, Permanent Representative of the United States to the United Nations in Geneva, and <a href=\"/wiki/Michael_M%C3%B8ller\" title=\"Michael M\u00f8ller\">Michael M\u00f8ller</a>, the Under-Secretary-General of the <a href=\"/wiki/United_Nations\" title=\"United Nations\">United Nations</a> and current Director-General of the <a href=\"/wiki/United_Nations_Office_at_Geneva\" title=\"United Nations Office at Geneva\">United Nations Office at Geneva</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Purpose\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Purpose</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Network\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Network</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Impact_Groups\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Impact Groups</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Events</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Purpose\">Purpose</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=International_Gender_Champions&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Purpose\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Champions pledge to no longer sit on single sex panels, and commit to implementing two individual institutional commitments for gender equality in their work.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> According to co-founder Caitlin Kraft-Buchman, International Gender Champions\u2019 strategy is to help make a wide range of organizations make \u201chuge changes through tiny steps\u201d by committing to realistic, achievable transformations for gender equality.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>At the IGC launch in 2015, M\u00f8ller stated, \u201cWith the unique concentration of Member States, international organizations, civil society, research and academic institutions and private sector entities, International Geneva provides an ideal platform to show that leadership in a most practical way.  Together, our actions have a truly global impact, making a difference for peace, rights and well-being for all people across the planet.  We have a special responsibility to capitalize on this potential for greater gender equality.\u201d<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Network\">Network</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=International_Gender_Champions&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Network\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>There are currently over 200 International Gender Champions in <a href=\"/wiki/Geneva\" title=\"Geneva\">Geneva</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/New_York_City\" title=\"New York City\">New York</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Vienna\" title=\"Vienna\">Vienna</a>, and <a href=\"/wiki/Nairobi\" title=\"Nairobi\">Nairobi</a>. Champions include UN Secretary General <a href=\"/wiki/Ant%C3%B3nio_Guterres\" title=\"Ant\u00f3nio Guterres\">Ant\u00f3nio Guterres</a>, the heads of UN Offices at Geneva, Vienna, and Nairobi, the <a href=\"/wiki/ILO\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"ILO\">ILO</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/World_Health_Organization\" title=\"World Health Organization\">WHO</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/World_Trade_Organization\" title=\"World Trade Organization\">WTO</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/World_Intellectual_Property_Organization\" title=\"World Intellectual Property Organization\">WIPO</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/International_Telecommunication_Union\" title=\"International Telecommunication Union\">ITU</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/UNHCR\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"UNHCR\">UNHCR</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/OHCHR\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"OHCHR\">OHCHR</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Inter-Parliamentary_Union\" title=\"Inter-Parliamentary Union\">IPU</a>, and other member states and civil society groups.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> After joining IGC, Secretary General Guterres stated, \u201cI encourage other senior leaders to be part of this campaign for equality. In a male dominated world, the empowerment of women must be a key priority. Women\u2019s rights are human rights \u2013 and attacks on women are attacks on all of us. Our world needs more women leaders. And our world needs more men standing up for gender equality.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Impact_Groups\">Impact Groups</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=International_Gender_Champions&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Impact Groups\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>IGC has organized impact groups, led by Champions which channel sector knowledge in greater detail on Representation, Trade, Change Management, Disarmament, and Standards.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> On the occasion of the <a href=\"/wiki/World_Trade_Organization\" title=\"World Trade Organization\">World Trade Organization\u2019s</a> Ministerial Conference in <a href=\"/wiki/Buenos_Aires\" title=\"Buenos Aires\">Buenos Aires</a> in December 2017, the IGC Trade Impact Group was joined by 120 WTO members and observers to issue the historic Joint Declaration on Trade and Women\u2019s Economic Empowerment, the first international declaration to explicitly link women\u2019s economic empowerment and trade.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> Susan Malcorra, who presided over the conference, called the Declaration a \u201cgreat success\u2026 Collectively, we were able to recognize the key role women can play in a fair, just and sustainable international trade system. The fact that so many countries, both members and observers of the WTO, rallied behind women\u2019s empowerment in this field signifies that not everything is lost.\u201d<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Events\">Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=International_Gender_Champions&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Events\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In 2017 and 2018, Geneva\u2019s <a href=\"/wiki/Jet_d%27Eau\" title=\"Jet d&#39;Eau\">Jet d\u2019Eau</a> was illuminated on International Women\u2019s Day with the turquoise of the International Gender Champions logo.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=International_Gender_Champions&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Solange Behoteguy and Garry Aslanyan, \u201cHow a \u2018table\u2019 could change the world,\u201d UN Special, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"https://www.unspecial.org/2016/03/how-a-table-could-change-the-world/\">https://www.unspecial.org/2016/03/how-a-table-could-change-the-world/</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Meg Riggs, \u201cInternational Gender Champions,\u201d Geneva Geeks, Podcast audio, March 31, 2017. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/id1224098484\">https://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/id1224098484</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Michael M\u00f8ller, \u201cInternational Geneva Gender Champions Launch: Director-General M\u00f8ller\u2019s Remarks,\u201d July 1, 2015, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"https://geneva.usmission.gov/2015/07/01/international-geneva-gender-champions-launch-director-general-mollers-remarks/\">https://geneva.usmission.gov/2015/07/01/international-geneva-gender-champions-launch-director-general-mollers-remarks/</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">About,\u201d International Gender Champions, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"https://genderchampions.com/about\">https://genderchampions.com/about</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Rita Emch, \u201cSwitzerland campaigns for equal pay at the UN,\u201d SWI, March 20, 2017, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/society/women-s-rights_switzerland-campaigns-for-equal-pay-at-the-un/43042664\">https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/society/women-s-rights_switzerland-campaigns-for-equal-pay-at-the-un/43042664</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\"Impact,\u201d International Gender Champions, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"https://genderchampions.com/impact\">https://genderchampions.com/impact</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Buenos Aires Declaration on Women and Trade outlines actions to empower women,\u201d World Trade Organization, December 21, 2017. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"https://www.wto.org/english/news_e/news17_e/mc11_12dec17_e.htm\">https://www.wto.org/english/news_e/news17_e/mc11_12dec17_e.htm</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/wiki/Susana_Malcorra\" title=\"Susana Malcorra\">Susana Malcorra</a>, \u201cEven amid Protectionism, Buenos Aires Gave Women Momentum,\u201d Centre for International Governance Innovation, April 2, 2018, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"https://www.cigionline.org/articles/even-amid-protectionism-buenos-aires-gave-women-momentum\">https://www.cigionline.org/articles/even-amid-protectionism-buenos-aires-gave-women-momentum</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\u201cInternational Women\u2019s Week,\u201d International Gender Champions, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"https://genderchampions.com/events/international-womens-week\">https://genderchampions.com/events/international-womens-week</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2164\nCached time: 20180920142729\nCache expiry: 190